{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:37:08.947Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying the Data**\n\nI'm thrilled; the mock data is perfect! Now, I'm meticulously verifying the specific requirements for the `/portal/ai-operations` page. I'm focusing on ensuring seamless integration and high fidelity within this context.\n\n\n**Defining the Dashboard Elements**\n\nI'm now concretely defining the page implementation! I have a solid draft: an \"Agent Health Overview\" with aggregated stats and status rails. I'm also planning \"Managed AI operations status\" with visual cues, and a dynamic \"Active agents\" grid, each with interactive elements like health rings and log containers. I'm designing action buttons that trigger realistic simulators.\n\n\n**Designing the Governance Checks**\n\nI'm now integrating governance checks into the design, including a table of items reflecting 'previewGovernanceItems' with compliance badges. I'm also planning a dynamic flow diagram or timeline to visualize the token/prompt transaction lifecycle, from Ingest through to Secure Client Outbound. I'm excited about the Control Center link and the emphasis on interactive filters.\n\n\n**Refining the UI Elements**\n\nI'm now diving deep into UI refinements, aiming for a premium, visually stunning dashboard. I'm focusing on incorporating a cohesive color palette with sovereign blue, GFF red, emerald-400, and amber-400. I'm also planning custom local animations like heartbeat waves and glowing borders. I plan to use Lucide icons for clarity and aesthetics, and I'm ensuring everything is super gorgeous. I'm checking for reusable components.\n\n\n**Integrating Reusable Components**\n\nI'm now determining reusable components. I can definitely import `PrivatePageHeader`, `WorkspaceCard`, `StatusBadge`, and `DataTable`. I'm considering using `DataTable` as-is, or building a bespoke table, or even a tabbed system incorporating both to get that super bespoke look. I'm focusing on \"Operational Log Ledger\" for a customized view within the page, keeping everything fully integrated.\n\nI'm refining interactive filters for real-time updates: Project (from `previewProjects`), Agent Type (mock categories), Status (active, evaluating, etc.), and Operating Stage (metadata-mapped). Now I'm preparing a complete list of 5 agents.\n\n\n"}}
