{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:37:38.421Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Verifying Tailwind Compatibility**\n\nI'm checking the codebase for Tailwind v4 compatibility. I've confirmed the use of Tailwind and related libraries, like tw-animate-css and shadcn/tailwind.css. Now, I'm carefully reviewing the CSS classes to ensure they're standard and compatible, with the goal to verify everything works as expected.\n\n\n**Designing the Command Center**\n\nI'm now focused on the internal design plan. The narrative emphasizes a multi-agent telemetry command center, highlighting physical isolation and cryptographic keys. My visual metaphor is a high-fidelity spacecraft cockpit. The layout strategy involves a responsive dashboard with warning banners, a header block, health overviews, and an interactive cockpit with dropdown filters. I'm focusing on incorporating radial health rings and real-time log tickers.\n\n\n**Refining UX Interactions**\n\nI'm now iterating on the user experience. I've designed a live grid of agent cards with circular health dials, logs, and a \"Recycle Enclave\" trigger. I'm focusing on dynamic tabbed workspaces, including architecture maps, governance checkpoints, and audit logs. I'm currently working on real-time React state tracking and interactive tab switching. Furthermore, I am implementing live search and select controls to refine the agent grid and focusing on making the grid mobile-responsive.\n\n\n**Implementing the Layout**\n\nI am now structuring the grid layout with `grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4` for metrics, ensuring excellent touch targets and mobile spacing with well-wrapped buttons and menus. I am also making sure to avoid nested boxes and overflow issues. My work focuses on `app/portal/ai-operations/page.tsx`, carefully replacing its contents. I am importing mock datasets, specifically `previewProjects` and `previewGovernanceItems`, and reviewing imports for accuracy.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Properties**\n\nI'm now enriching the agent data model for richer filtering. I'm examining `lib/mock-data-model.ts` to see how agent operations are defined. I'll extend the `previewAgentOperations` data, creating an `EnrichedAgent` type with custom properties for filtering, such as agent type, operating stage, and health. I am going to enrich the agent data to support more refined filtering options.\n\n\n**Implementing Health Rings**\n\nI'm now focusing on implementing the health rings. I've decided on using SVG circles with `strokeDasharray` and `strokeDashoffset` for an elegant solution. I'm building a reusable `<HealthRing>` component with parameters for value, size, stroke width, and color. I'm working to make the ring visually representative of the agent's health and performance.\n\n\n**Building the Health Ring**\n\nI'm now integrating the health ring component. I'm using an SVG circle with `strokeDasharray` and `strokeDashoffset` for the animation, ensuring the visual indicator works effectively. I'm currently setting up the `circumference` and `strokeDashoffset` calculations. I'm implementing a percentage text overlay for clear feedback on the agent's health state.\n\n\n**Designing Status Rails**\n\nI am now focusing on designing the Managed AI Operations status rail. I've broken it down into several distinct rails to represent different operational aspects. I am planning on the Physical Isolation rail, showing secure hardware enclave status, and a Dynamic Guardrail Matching Rail for real-time evaluation pipeline monitoring. I'll also add an eBPF Trace Visibility rail to show live thread and system process data.\n\n\n**Designing Status Rails**\n\nI am now focusing on designing more status rails, adding a BPF Kernel Network Rail to monitor system calls and a HSM Key Rotation Rail for cryptographic handshake status. I'm aiming for interactive progress indicators and hover details to enrich the visual feedback. I will also incorporate a narrative timeline of events, including key rotations and boundary verifications.\n\n\n**Refining Landing Page Header**\n\nI'm now iterating on the landing page header. I've designed a clear header with a prominent \"Sovereign Control Center Gateway\" title. The design emphasizes the \"INTEGRATED CONTROL HUB\" label and includes a concise description of the platform's capabilities. I'm focusing on a clean, modern aesthetic with specific colors and fonts for clarity.\n\n\n**Implementing the Entrance Button**\n\nI'm now integrating the \"Enter Control Center\" button with an `ArrowUpRight` icon, aiming for a premium and strategic look, perfectly aligning with the overall GFF AI aesthetic. The design needs to be fully implemented. I'm focusing on the component's interactive design.\n\nI've also started planning the agent filtering logic. I'm defining state variables for project, type, status, stage, and search, which I will use to filter the agent data.\n\n\n**Designing Enclave Interactions**\n\nI'm now implementing the \"Recycle Core Enclave\" action. I'm focusing on simulating the reboot with status updates and log messages. I'll include a loading spinner and a 1.8-second delay before restoring the \"active\" status. I'm also preparing to add interactive state diagrams. Finally, I'm verifying and testing all filter logic and associated visual indicators.\n\n\n"}}
